  "original_title": "Modi congratulates Dinesh",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Modi congratulates Dinesh",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi in a congratulatory letter has wished newly appointed Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena and assured India\u2019s support to the people of Sri Lanka.",
        "Gunawardena, 73, a veteran Politician was appointed as Sri Lanka\u2019s Prime Minister by President Ranil Wickremesinghe on 22 July.",
        "\u201cI would like to assure you as a dependable friend and close neighbour, India shall continue to support the people of Sri Lanka guided by our friend first policy,\u201d",
        "Modi in his letter said. He went on to express his hope that Sri Lanka will witness quick economic recovery under Gunawardena\u2019s leadership ensuring the prosperity and well-being of the country\u2019s people.",
        "Last week, Modi also congratulated President Wickremesinghe and said that India will continue to be supportive of the quest of the people of the island nation for stability and economic recovery, through established democratic means."
      ],
